        <p>Here's the JavaScript that adds our custom rule / method initialises the validation.  The name of the custom rule / method is the same as the <code>ValidationType</code> specified on the attribute. And if you look at the <code>params</code> parameter you can see this is the client side equivalent of our <code>ValidationParameters</code> Dictionary on the attribute.  As you can see from the method we use the <code>other</code> property to look up our comparison element. The <code>"These shouldn't equal"</code> string is the default error message that will be displayed if an <code>ErrorMessage</code> hasn't been specified when the attribute has been used.</p>

